<paragraph id="260CE532077B841C02CFE461750CFED1" blockId="17.[151,1436,1883,2016]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="17" pageNumber="144">
Abdomen and legs: Underside punctate and pubescent. Legs moderately long, femora robust, mid- and hindtibiae slightly curved. Pygidium exposed, convex, apical margin straight, punctate and pubescent laterally. Median lobe flattened, slightly curved, widest nearly in the middle, basal and apical portions narrow, sclerotised except dorsocentral portion membranous, apical lamella triangular, blunt, slightly swollen laterally (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B7077B841F06B9E4FD7306F82C" box="[1201,1334,1991,2016]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–45" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1344,359,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1435,337,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40–45. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Aedeagus, lateral view; 41. Median lobe and median struts, ventral view; 42. Median lobe, dorsal view; 43. Tegmen, dorsal view; 44. Tegmen, lateral view; 45. Spiculum, dorsal view; Abbreviations: median lobe (Mdl); median struts (Mds); spiculum (Spi); tegmen (Teg); endophallus (Edp); paramere (Par); tegminal ring (Tgr); basal piece (Bpi); Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457043/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="144">Figs 40–42</figureCitation>
); median struts rod-shaped, widely separated from each other, approximately 2.6 times as long as median lobe (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70778841C0704E3AD73A0FF7C" box="[1292,1424,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–45" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1344,359,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1435,337,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40–45. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Aedeagus, lateral view; 41. Median lobe and median struts, ventral view; 42. Median lobe, dorsal view; 43. Tegmen, dorsal view; 44. Tegmen, lateral view; 45. Spiculum, dorsal view; Abbreviations: median lobe (Mdl); median struts (Mds); spiculum (Spi); tegmen (Teg); endophallus (Edp); paramere (Par); tegminal ring (Tgr); basal piece (Bpi); Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457043/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="145">Figs 40–41</figureCitation>
); tegmen with basal portion V-shaped, paramere lingulate, apical margin pubescent (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70778841C067AE38672CBFF18" box="[1138,1275,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–45" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1344,359,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1435,337,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40–45. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Aedeagus, lateral view; 41. Median lobe and median struts, ventral view; 42. Median lobe, dorsal view; 43. Tegmen, dorsal view; 44. Tegmen, lateral view; 45. Spiculum, dorsal view; Abbreviations: median lobe (Mdl); median struts (Mds); spiculum (Spi); tegmen (Teg); endophallus (Edp); paramere (Par); tegminal ring (Tgr); basal piece (Bpi); Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457043/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="145">Figs 43–44</figureCitation>
); endophallus membranous, with two slightly round pieces of spiny areasat apex (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70778841C01A2E3E57201FF34" box="[938,1073,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–45" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1344,359,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1435,337,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40–45. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Aedeagus, lateral view; 41. Median lobe and median struts, ventral view; 42. Median lobe, dorsal view; 43. Tegmen, dorsal view; 44. Tegmen, lateral view; 45. Spiculum, dorsal view; Abbreviations: median lobe (Mdl); median struts (Mds); spiculum (Spi); tegmen (Teg); endophallus (Edp); paramere (Par); tegminal ring (Tgr); basal piece (Bpi); Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457043/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="145">Figs 40–41</figureCitation>
). Spiculum slightly longer than median lobe, basestick-shaped and apex triangular (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70778841C00D3E23E751FFED1" box="[731,815,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–45" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1344,359,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1435,337,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40–45. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Aedeagus, lateral view; 41. Median lobe and median struts, ventral view; 42. Median lobe, dorsal view; 43. Tegmen, dorsal view; 44. Tegmen, lateral view; 45. Spiculum, dorsal view; Abbreviations: median lobe (Mdl); median struts (Mds); spiculum (Spi); tegmen (Teg); endophallus (Edp); paramere (Par); tegminal ring (Tgr); basal piece (Bpi); Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457043/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="145">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
