<subSubSection id="6EA9B6B90779841D02CFE38675DCFF19" box="[199,1004,188,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="260CE5320779841D02CFE38675DCFF19" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,1004,188,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D02CFE386777EFF19" bold="true" box="[199,334,188,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D002AE38774ACFF18" authorityName="Li &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" box="[546,668,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroapica">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D002AE38774ACFF18" box="[546,668,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">nigroapica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to apex of elytra black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EA9B6B90779841D02CFE3E5754FFD48" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="260CE5320779841D02CFE3E57542FE60" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D02CFE3E5770BFF34" bold="true" box="[199,315,223,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D007DE3DA75E9FF3B" authority="Li &amp; Liang, 2018" authorityName="Li &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" box="[629,985,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeica" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pedrillia">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D007DE3DA74CEFF34" box="[629,766,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Zeugophora</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D011BE3DA7547FF34" box="[787,887,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Pedrillia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D0182E3DA75E9FF3B" box="[906,985,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">emeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0FF4845B0779841D01ECE3DA7271FF3B" box="[996,1089,224,247]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs from the latter in having: 1) pronotum entirely black, elytra with lager black area at apex, most portion of legs black, apex of elytra more convex (basal margin of pronotum reddish brown, elytra with less black area at apex, most portion of legs reddish brown in 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D036AE2777431FEA8" authorityName="Li &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" box="[354,513,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeica" subGenus="Pedrillia">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D036AE2777749FEA8" box="[354,377,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Z.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D0383E27777ADFEA8" box="[395,413,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D03BAE2777431FEA8" box="[434,513,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">emeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) median lobe elongate, apical lamella slightly swollen laterally, median strut long, tegmen slightly sclerotised (base of median lobe broad, apical lamella strongly narrowed and downward, median strut short, tegmen strongly sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D00CFE2AF7551FE60" authorityName="Li &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" box="[711,865,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeica" subGenus="Pedrillia">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D00CFE2AF74EEFE60" box="[711,734,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Z.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D00E5E2AF7530FE60" box="[749,768,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D011AE2AF7551FE60" box="[786,865,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">emeica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="260CE5320779841D02CFE28D754FFD48" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">
This species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D0013E2827227FE1C" authority="Kraatz, 1879" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1879" box="[539,1047,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="Pedrillia">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D0013E2827494FE1C" box="[539,676,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Zeugophora</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D00BDE2827529FE1C" box="[693,793,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Pedrillia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D0122E282754BFE1C" box="[810,891,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">bicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="422298C30779841D018AE2827227FE1C" box="[898,1047,440,464]" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" refId="ref13079" refString="Kraatz, G. (1879) Neue Kafer vom Amur. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 23, 121 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 48018790117" type="journal article">Kraatz, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter in having: 1) apex of elytra black, pronotum entirely black, pronotum with two basal tubercles (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70779841D0737E2E673A4FE39" box="[1343,1428,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1755,1778]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,217,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male. 35. Dorsal view; 36. Ventral view; 37. Head, anterior view; 38. Pronotum, dorsal view; 39. Apex of elytra, posterior view. Scale line = 2.0 mm (Figs 35–36); Scale line = 0.5 mm (Figs 37–39)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457041/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) (elytra entirely yellowish brown, basal portion of pronotum reddish brown, pronotum with basal tubercle absent in 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D029FE11F770AFDF0" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,314,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="Pedrillia">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D029FE11F769EFDF0" box="[151,174,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Z.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D02CAE11F76E4FDF0" box="[194,212,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D02E3E11E770AFDF0" box="[235,314,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70779841D0344E11E7794FDF1" box="[332,420,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–48" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1516,1539]" captionTargetBox="[186,1327,488,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,477,1495]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 46–48. Zeugophora (Pedrillia) bicolor Kraatz, 1879 from Liaoning (China), male. 46. Habitus, dorsal view; 47. Median lobe and median struts, lateral view; 48. Median lobe, dorsal view. Scale line = 2.0 mm (Fig. 46); Scale line = 0.5 mm (Fig. 47); Scale line = 0.2 mm (Fig. 48)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); 2) dorsocentral portion of median lobe membranous, widest in the middle, narrowed basally and apically (
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70779841D0380E17D743BFDAC" box="[392,523,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–45" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1344,359,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1435,337,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40–45. Holotype of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigroapica sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Aedeagus, lateral view; 41. Median lobe and median struts, ventral view; 42. Median lobe, dorsal view; 43. Tegmen, dorsal view; 44. Tegmen, lateral view; 45. Spiculum, dorsal view; Abbreviations: median lobe (Mdl); median struts (Mds); spiculum (Spi); tegmen (Teg); endophallus (Edp); paramere (Par); tegminal ring (Tgr); basal piece (Bpi); Scale line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457043/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Figs 41, 42</figureCitation>
) (basal one third portion of median lobe tubular, the rest of dorsocentral portion membranous, lateral margins paralleled in 
<taxonomicName id="E1B39EB10779841D007DE1577520FD48" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1879" box="[629,784,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="Pedrillia">
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D007DE15774BCFD48" box="[629,652,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Z.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D0094E157749EFD48" box="[668,686,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="14C739200779841D00C9E1567520FD48" box="[705,784,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<figureCitation id="BE88F9B70779841D0116E1567542FD48" box="[798,882,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–48" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1516,1539]" captionTargetBox="[186,1327,488,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[150,1436,477,1495]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 46–48. Zeugophora (Pedrillia) bicolor Kraatz, 1879 from Liaoning (China), male. 46. Habitus, dorsal view; 47. Median lobe and median struts, lateral view; 48. Median lobe, dorsal view. Scale line = 2.0 mm (Fig. 46); Scale line = 0.5 mm (Fig. 47); Scale line = 0.2 mm (Fig. 48)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="146">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
